{{refimprove|date=August 2014}} {{About|the theatre in Chicago||Court Theatre (disambiguation){{!}}Court Theatre}} [[File:Inside Court Theatre, Chicago.jpg|thumb]] The '''Court Theatre''' is a professional theatre located in the [[Hyde Park, Chicago|Hyde Park]] neighborhood of [[Chicago, Illinois]]. The Court Theatre is affiliated with the [[University of Chicago]], receiving in-kind support from the University and operating within the larger University umbrella. The Court Theatre puts on five plays per season which are attended by over 35,000 people each year.
Established in 1955.
Charles Newell has been Artistic Director since 1994, and in 2010 was joined by Stephen J. Albert as Executive Director.
