{{Infobox radio station |name = WHPK |image = [[Image:Whpk.png]] |city = [[Chicago]] |area = |branding = |slogan = The Pride of the South Side<ref name=About>{{cite web|url=http://www.whpk.org/about/|title=About|first=|last=|date=|publisher=WHPK|accessdate=February 26, 2012}}</ref> |frequency = 88.5 [[MHz]] |translator = |repeater = |airdate = {{start date|1968|3|22}}<ref name=UoCChronicle1995/> |share = |share as of = |share source = |format = [[College radio]], [[community radio]] |language = |erp = 100 [[watt]]s |haat = {{convert|37|m|sp=us}} |class = A ([[non-commercial educational|NCE]]) |facility_id = 69000 |coordinates = |callsign_meaning = [[Woodlawn, Chicago|'''W'''oodlawn]]/[[Hyde Park, Chicago|'''H'''yde '''P'''ark]]/[[Kenwood, Chicago|'''K'''enwood]]<ref name=UoCChronicle1995/> |former_callsigns = WHPK-FM (1968-2016) |former_frequencies = 88.3 MHz (1968&ndash;1985) |affiliations = |owner = [[University of Chicago]] |licensee = |sister_stations = |webcast = |website = {{url|http://www.whpk.org/}}}}
'''WHPK''' (88.5 [[FM radio|FM]])<ref name=TimeOutChi2011/> is an American [[radio station]] based in [[Hyde Park, Chicago|Hyde Park]] on the [[South Side, Chicago|South Side of Chicago]], established in 1968. The station is owned by the [[University of Chicago]], and operated by volunteer students and community members. WHPK's station manager and program director are elected by the station's student members and must be students themselves. The station's [[Broadcast engineering|broadcast engineer]] is paid by the university.
==History== [[Image:Reynoldsclub.JPG|thumb|left|150px|Mitchell Tower, [[University of Chicago]] Reynolds Club building where the station's studios are located.]] In 1968, WHPK-FM was established when the campus secret Society of the Owl and Serpent disbanded, donating its funds and Reynolds Club office space to a student radio group. WHPK-FM started broadcasting as a 15-watt FM station at 88.3&nbsp;MHz on March 22, 1968. In 1985, WHPK-FM upgraded to a 100-watt transmitter and moved to the current frequency of 88.5&nbsp;MHz.<ref name=UoCChronicle1995>{{cite news|url=http://chronicle.uchicago.edu/951207/whpk.shtml|title=WHPK: Still spinnin' {{sic|hide=y|after}} all these years|first=|last=|date=December 7, 1995|publisher=University of Chicago Chronicle|volume=15|issue=7|accessdate=June 26, 2008}}</ref>
WHPK-FM was the first radio station to broadcast [[hip hop]] music in Chicago, and would become home to aspiring rappers throughout the years, including [[Common (rapper)|Common]]<ref name=TimeOutChi2011>{{cite news|url=http://timeoutchicago.com/arts-culture/1204037/chicago-memories-common|title=Chicago memories: Common|first=Jake|last=Austen|date=April 27, 2011|publisher=Time Out Chicago|accessdate=February 26, 2011}}</ref> and [[Kanye West]].<ref name=UoC2011-2>{{cite news|url=https://www.uchicago.edu/features/20111205_whpk/sidebar.shtml|title=WHPK hosted Common/Kanye faceoff—before they were stars|first=Michael|last=Drapa|date=December 5, 2011|publisher=University of Chicago|accessdate=February 26, 2011}}</ref>
The station changed its call sign to the current WHPK on February 26, 2016.
==Content== Programming blocks are divided into [[classical music|classical]], [[folk music|folk]], [[world music|international]], [[jazz]], [[Public affairs programming|public affairs]], [[Hip hop music|rap]], [[Rock music|rock]], and specialty show formats.<ref name=About/>
===Notable=== In 1984, WHPK-FM's first rap show was established by Ken Wissoker.<ref name=UoC2011-1>{{cite news|url=https://www.uchicago.edu/features/20111205_whpk/index.shtml|title=Pioneering WHPK keeps Chicago rap fresh|first=Tomi|last=Obaro|date=December 5, 2011|publisher=University of Chicago|accessdate=February 26, 2011}}</ref> DJ JP Chill has had a rap and hip hop show on WHPK since 1986.<ref name=Tribune2005>{{cite news|url=http://articles.chicagotribune.com/2006-07-16/news/0607160012_1_hip-hop-heads-turntable-scratches-dj-nu-mark/2|title=Chicago Hip-hop History ... A Tour|first=Patrick|last=Sisson|date=July 16, 2006|publisher=''[[Chicago Tribune]]''|accessdate=February 26, 2011}}</ref>
A long-running Saturday night show, ''The Blues Excursion'', is hosted by a widely received radio personality named Arkansas Red.<ref name=Tribune1993>{{cite news|url=http://articles.chicagotribune.com/1993-05-30/features/9305300445_1_weekly-blues-conversational-gospel|title=Arkansas Red's House Party: Weekly Blues, Talk Show Has South Side Listening|first=Clifford|last=Terry|date=May 30, 1993|publisher=''Chicago Tribune''|accessdate=February 26, 2011}}</ref>
==Recognition== In 2008, WHPK-FM was awarded "Best College Radio Station" by ''[[Chicago Reader]]''.<ref name=ChicagoReader2008>{{cite web|url=http://www.chicagoreader.com/bestofchicago08/media/collegeradio/|title=Best of Chicago 2008 - Reader’s Choice: WHPK|first=|last=|year=2008|publisher=''[[Chicago Reader]]''|accessdate=June 26, 2008}}</ref>
